@Data
public class Garden {
    private int length;
    private int width;
    private int area;

    public static void main(String[] args) {
        Garden garden = new Garden();
        garden.setWidth(8);
        garden.setArea(184);
        garden.setLength(garden.getArea() / garden.getWidth());
        System.out.println(garden.getLength());
    }
}

The length of the common side (which is the other dimension of the garden) can be calculated by dividing the area of the garden by the known width. Given that the area is 184 square feet and the width is 8 feet, the calculation would be $184 \div 8 = 23$ feet. Thus, the length of the common side is 23 feet.

$\boxed{23}$

